      "text": "Important point of the Federated Wiki is that people don't have to agree. They can fork each other's pages to their own wiki, and if they disagree on something they can change them. If they do agree they can reference each other. If they just agree with one paragraph they can take this paragraph onto their page, without any additional hassle of referencing the origin, because it is automatically referenced."
