      "id": "456e186640829b88",
      "text": "I have a case in which it can be useful. When I started with the Federated Wiki in March 3 of us started writing about cryptocurrencies. So we made 4 wikis - one personal wiki each (with the name) like [http://ksenya.cryptoacademy.org/ this one] and the \"central one\" to which we decided to fork \"finished\" content, so it looks presentable to people who are not necessarily into FedWiki, but want to browse around for material about cryptocurrencies. It was a bit of a mess. every time I would spend some time researching a topic and would make a whole load of pages which would be good in the \"central\" wiki, I had to ping a person who owned it and ask \"Can you fork this, vcan you fork that\" etc. "
